What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Flaxseed Oil Market?

Flaxseed Oil Market Analysis and Size

The global flaxseed oil market is experiencing steady growth, driven by increasing consumer awareness of the health benefits associated with flaxseed oil consumption. Flaxseed oil is rich in alpha-linolenic acid (ALA), an omega-3 fatty acid that is known for its anti-inflammatory and heart-healthy properties. As consumers become more health-conscious and seek out natural remedies, the demand for flaxseed oil as a dietary supplement is on the rise. Flaxseed oil is also gaining popularity in the food industry, where it is used as a cooking oil and salad dressing due to its nutty flavor and nutritional benefits.

Global flaxseed oil market size was valued at USD 5.36 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 7.06 billion by 2031, with a CAGR of 3.5% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

